text: Zhu Xueying is a Chinese trampoline gymnast. In 2017, she won two gold medals at the 2017 Trampoline Gymnastics World Championships held in Sofia, Bulgaria. In 2018, she won the silver medal in the women's individual event at the 2018 Trampoline Gymnastics World Championships held in Saint Petersburg, Russia. In 2014, she won the gold medal in the girls' trampoline event at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics held in Nanjing, China. == References == == External links == * Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Chinese female trampolinists Category:Gymnasts at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Medalists at the Trampoline Gymnastics World Championships Category:Youth Olympic gold medalists for China
